<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7652] Float/Double trunc methods perform rounding for negative values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7652</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;trunc&lt;/tt&gt; methods on Float/Double use the &lt;tt&gt;Math.floor&lt;/tt&gt; method for all values, however for negative values this causing rounding.  I think for negative values &lt;tt&gt;Math.ceil&lt;/tt&gt; needs to be used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are some asserts to show the rounding:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt; f = -123.739f
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Double&lt;/span&gt; d = -123.739d

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; -123f == f.trunc() &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// fails: -124
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; -123d == d.trunc() &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// fails: -124
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt;&#8203; -123.73f == f.trunc(2)&#8203; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// fails: -123.74
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; -123.73d == d.trunc(2) &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// fails: -123.73&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
